<TITLE> 100 shanties burn in Mirpur fire </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 6 (bdnews24.com)  Over a hundred shanties were burnt down when a devastating blaze raged through a slum in Mirpur in the capital late Monday morning, fire officials and locals said. They said the fire broke out at around 11:30am at the slum near the Janata Housing in Mirpur-2. Fire Service officer Abdur Rashid told bdnews24.com they tamed the flames at 12: 45pm. They could not immediately say the source of the fire nor was the count of casualties available. bd
